body:
Reported by an user on discord.

It seems like there is a small bug in teku `23.10.0` beacon node. When running on holesky, the fork schedule endpoint (/eth/v1/config/fork_schedule) gives the following response:

```json
{
   "data":[
      {
         "previous_version":"0x01017000",
         "current_version":"0x01017000",
         "epoch":"0"
      },
      {
         "previous_version":"0x02017000",
         "current_version":"0x02017000",
         "epoch":"0"
      },
      {
         "previous_version":"0x03017000",
         "current_version":"0x03017000",
         "epoch":"0"
      },
      {
         "previous_version":"0x03017000",
         "current_version":"0x04017000", 
         "epoch":"256"
      }
   ]
}
```

While it should be:
```json
{
   "data":[
      {
         "previous_version":"0x01017000",
         "current_version":"0x01017000",
         "epoch":"0"
      },
      {
         "previous_version":"0x01017000",
         "current_version":"0x02017000",
         "epoch":"0"
      },
      {
         "previous_version":"0x02017000",
         "current_version":"0x03017000",
         "epoch":"0"
      },
      {
         "previous_version":"0x03017000",
         "current_version":"0x04017000", 
         "epoch":"256"
      }
   ]
}
```
